Package org.codehaus.preon.codec

The package providing some default CodecFactories, supporting a number of different Codecs.

See:
          Description

Class Summary
ArrayCodecFactory A CodecFactory that will be triggered by Bound or BoundList annotations on arrays.
BindingsContext A ResolverContext based on a collection of Bindings.
BooleanCodecFactory A CodecFactory capable of creating Codecs that deal with booleans.
BoundBufferCodecFactory  
ByteAligningDecorator A CodecDecorator that will make sure that reading stops at a byte-aligned position.
CachingCodecFactory An implementation of the CodecFactory interface that will prevent the same Codec from being constructed twice.
CompoundCodecFactory A CodecFactory capable of generating Codecs by delegating to a sorted list of other CodecFactories.
EnumCodec<T> Created by IntelliJ IDEA.
EnumCodec.Factory A CodecFactory creating Codecs capable of decoding enum values.
ExplicitCodecFactory A CodecFactory allowing you to explicitly set the Codec to use.
FixedLengthStringCodec A Codec decoding Strings based on a fixed number of bytes.
InitCodecDecorator A decorator that will inspect all methods on the object constructed by the Codec to be decorated, and create a decorated Codec that will invoke a method after the object has been constructed, based on the Init annotation.
LazyLoadingCodecDecorator An attempt to create a general purpose CodecFactory whose Codecs will only load their data once operations are invoked upon them.
LazyLoadingCodecDecorator.LazyLoadingCodec<T> A Codec that will only start loading the data when one of the methods of that object are invoked.
ListBasedMapCodec<K,V> Created by IntelliJ IDEA.
ListCodecFactory A CodecFactory capable of supporting Lists.
MapCodecFactory  
NullTerminatedStringCodec A Codec that reads null-terminated Strings.
NumericCodec The Codec capable of decoding numeric types in a sensible way.
NumericCodec.Factory A CodecFactory generating Codecs capable of decoding numbers from the BitBuffer.
ObjectCodec<T> The Codec capable of decoding instances of arbitrary classes.
ObjectCodecFactory The CodecFactory for ObjectCodecs.
PurposeDecorator  
SelectFromCodec<T> A Codec supporting the Choices annotation.
SlicingCodecDecorator A CodecFactory creating Codecs slicing the BitBuffer to limit the visibility of the remainder of the buffer (and easily skip forward, if the data itself is not required).
StringCodecFactory A CodecFactory generating Codecs capable of generating String from BitBuffer content.
SwitchingCodec A Codec that is able to dynamically choose between different types of objects to decode, based on a couple of leading bits.
TypePrefixSelectorFactory A CodecSelectorFactory that will create a CodecSelector that will look for leading bits, matching a certain value expressed with an TypePrefix annotation on the Codecs classes.
